<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFC9FFE2FF8DFCB5FE3AFAFA" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC9FFE2FF8DFCB5FDCEFB5A" blockId="19.[113,1089,851,1386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FF8DFCB5FF5EFCDA" bold="true" box="[113,224,851,874]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FF1AFCB5FE26FCDA" author="BOHEMAN" box="[230,408,851,874]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
described this species presumably from a single specimen from the collection of Chevrolat. He compared it with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FD7FFC95FBADFC3A" authority="(Fabricius, 1798)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[643,1043,883,906]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FD7FFC95FCEDFC3A" box="[643,851,883,906]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Coptocycla clavata</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1798)
</taxonomicName>
and it was placed in the same group as other species latter transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FC31FC75FF44FC7A" authority="Spaeth, 1952" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Helocassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FC31FC75FBFFFC1A" box="[973,1089,915,938]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Helocassis</emphasis>
Spaeth, 1952
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FEDEFC55FE15FC7A" author="HINCKS" box="[290,427,947,970]" firstAuthor="HINCKS" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" pagination="327 - 358" refId="ref49715" refString="HINCKS W. D. 1952: The genera of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 103: 327 - 358." type="journal article" year="1952">HINCKS 1952</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FE47FC55FDEEFC7A" author="SPAETH" box="[443,592,947,970]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" pagination="135 - 158" refId="ref51390" refString="SPAETH F. 1937: Neue Cassidinen des Rijksmuseums in Leiden und meiner Sammlung. Temminckia 2: 135 - 158." type="journal article" year="1937">SPAETH (1937)</bibRefCitation>
however, placed 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FCF9FC55FC6DFC7A" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[773,979,947,970]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FCF9FC55FC6DFC7A" box="[773,979,947,970]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Coptocycla ramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FC0DFC55FED8FC5A" authority="Spaeth, 1899" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FC0DFC55FF6FFC5A" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FF24FC35FED8FC5A" author="Spaeth" box="[216,358,979,1002]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" pagination="213 - 221" refId="ref50724" refString="SPAETH F. 1899: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen III. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 49: 213 - 221 + pl. 5." type="journal article" year="1899">Spaeth, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, most likely based on the primary description. I have studied its 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC9FFE2FBEFFC35FBFFFC5A" box="[1043,1089,979,1002]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
and the species in fact belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FE2AFC15FDF4FBBA" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1952" box="[470,586,1011,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Helocassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FE2AFC15FDF4FBBA" box="[470,586,1011,1034]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Helocassis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it has a head with frontoclypeal sulci, which are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FF00FBF5FE1DFB9A" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[252,419,1043,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FF00FBF5FE1DFB9A" box="[252,419,1043,1066]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FC58FBF5FE90FBFA" authority="(Boheman, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Helocassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FC58FBF5FBFEFB9A" box="[932,1088,1043,1066]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">H. crucipennis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FF85FBD5FE99FBFA" author="Boheman" box="[121,295,1075,1098]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the base of elytra much wider than the base of pronotum, humeral angles protruding anterad, and subpentagonal body outline with straight lateral sides of elytra while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FEE5FB95FE06FB3A" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[281,440,1139,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Helocassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FEE5FB95FE06FB3A" box="[281,440,1139,1162]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">H. crucipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has oval body with weakly projecting humeral angles. The body shape is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FE42FB75FC99FB1A" authority="(Boheman, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[446,807,1171,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Helocassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testudinaria">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FE42FB75FDDCFB1A" box="[446,610,1171,1194]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">H. testudinaria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FD8EFB75FC9EFB1A" author="Boheman" box="[626,800,1171,1194]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FCA3FB75FC71FB1A" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[863,975,1171,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FCA3FB75FC71FB1A" box="[863,975,1171,1194]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">H. clavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, both have rugose surface of elytra and high postscutellar tubercle, which is very low in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC9FFE2FBDBFB55FF7FFB5A" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC9FFE2FBDBFB55FF7FFB5A" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">H. ramosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it also has smooth surface of elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC9FFE2FF6CFB15FE3AFAFA" blockId="19.[113,1089,851,1386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC9FFE2FF6CFB15FEFFFABA" author="BOHEMAN" box="[144,321,1267,1290]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="19" pageNumber="294" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned ‘Columbia’ as the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC9FFE2FD7CFB15FD10FABA" box="[640,686,1267,1290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
locality, however, the specimen bears more detailed locality data. The 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC9FFE2FE3EFAF5FE4EFA9A" box="[450,496,1299,1322]" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
locality is here specified to Honda situated in the 
<collectingRegion id="2D12B0D4FFC9FFE2FC09FAF5FF51FAFA" country="Colombia" name="Tolima" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Tolima Department</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFC9FFE2FEEFFAD5FE3EFAFA" box="[275,384,1331,1354]" name="Colombia" pageId="19" pageNumber="294">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
